web root is also "/"  ie project.com/

relative path accessed by ./  (this directory/same folder)
path accessed by .// (parent directory)

cmd shift square brackets to jump tabs


ELEMENTS

center - box-sizing:border-box

if want to have object centered left and right - * elements need width and max width
    display:block;
    margin:auto;

means there will be 30px margin around element
div{
  margin:30px    - top only
  margin:30px 20px - top, right/left
  margin:30px 20px 80px - top, left/right, bottom
  margin:30px 20px 80px 100px   - top, right, bottom, left
}


STYLING
1. Focus on LAYOUT!
    put everything in colored boxes
    can inspect element and select element to see and inspect

2. Line things up!
    make spacing "even"
    and have few visual "axis"

3. Clean simple text!
    3 fonts at most
    only 1 font that pops
      San-serif typically used for web or large bodies and books
      google fonts import into style.css or before all main script

* default body font size makes <p> = 1em, makes all h1, p relational to that
rem - sizing is relative to base font
% is percent of parent, does not work for fonts
width and height = max-width works best
if nothing use just zero (0) without measurement


BACKGROUNDS
can apply background to anything
background-size: cover (auto fills height and width)  contain (auto width)
bg-repeat: no-repeat

body {
  background-image:
  background-repeat:
  background-size:
  background-position:
}


